can be busy, mainly when the lavender fields are in bloom(July &amp; August) and the gorgeous beaches of the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/france\/french-riviera-travel-guide\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Cote d&#x2019;Azur<\/a> are at their best. However, it&#x2019;s a great time to take advantage of kayaking and swimming in the numerous waterfalls and rivers of the region.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/22102830\/provence-1.jpg\" alt=\"things to do provence france gordes\"><\/noscript><img width=\"270\" height=\"338\" alt=\"things to do provence france gordes\" class=\"wp-image-69930 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1536px) 100vw, 1536px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/22102830\/provence-1.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/22102830\/provence-1-480x600.jpg 480w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/22102830\/provence-1-648x810.jpg 648w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/22102830\/provence-1-270x338.jpg 270w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/22102830\/provence-1-24x30.jpg 24w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/22102830\/provence-1-130x163.jpg 130w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/22102830\/provence-1-144x180.jpg 144w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/22102830\/provence-1-614x768.jpg 614w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/22102830\/provence-1-819x1024.jpg 819w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/22102830\/provence-1-864x1080.jpg 864w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/22102830\/provence-1-1152x1440.jpg 1152w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/22102830\/provence-1-300x375.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/22102830\/provence-1-600x750.jpg 600w\" tempsrc=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/22102830\/provence-1-24x30.jpg\" src=\"\/build\/images\/blank.png\" onerror=\"this.srcset='\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.src='\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.classList.remove('lazypreload'); \"><a class=\"pinit\" href=\"https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-pin=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/22102830\/provence-1.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2 id=\"restaurants\">Best Cafes and Restaurants in Provence<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Food and wine are life in Provence, and the locals are very proud of their delicious regional produce. There are weekly markets held in every village where you can sample delicacies and buy some to take home, as well as the option to visit wineries and Provencal farms. In every town, you&#x2019;ll also find beautiful restaurants, where you can sit on the terrace in the mild evening temperatures. Some of our favorites in Provence were:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>La Bastide de Pierres (Gordes)<\/li><li>Le Petit Caf&#xE9; (Oppede)<\/li><li>La Grappe de Raisin (Roussillon)<\/li><li>Le Petit Proven&#xE7;al (Manosque)<\/li><li>La Table Toscane (Riez)<\/li><li>Comptoir de Val&#xE9;rie (Valensole)<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/22103729\/provence-restaurants-2-540x810.jpg\" alt=\"french restaurant\"><\/noscri